Removing `self.N` is not entirely trivial since `create_filters(self)` needs it in `self` to call `scattering_filter_factory` with `self.N` as first argument.
But i could easily rename it to `self._N` so that it does not appear to the user in `self.+TAB`

If we change our minds later and think that `self.N` (by which i mean, the padded N, not the input length `shape[0]`) should be made public, we could do:

```python
@property
def N(self):
    return len(self.phi_f[0]))
```

in this way, the integer in `self._N` will only serve to carry across the output of `compute_temporal_support` (called in `self.build()`) over to the input of `scattering_filter_factory` (called in `self.create_filters()`)
